      <sourceDesc>
        <listWit>
          <witness xml:id="Pt4">1779-80, Bodleian Library Oxford (MS. Zend d.2)</witness>
          <witness xml:id="F2">1813, two volumes, First Dastur Meherji Rana Library</witness>
          <witness xml:id="J2">1323, Bodleian Library Oxford</witness>
          <witness xml:id="M1">1734, a copy of K5, Königliche Hof- und Staatsbibliothek</witness>
        </listWit>
      </sourceDesc>
    </fileDesc>
    <encodingDesc>
      <projectDesc>
        <p>The proposed work on the exegetical Yasna aims at providing not only a text-
          critical edition in the form of a print output but also at creating a database of
          manuscript readings. In preparation for major research grant applications, two main 
          research questions need to be addressed in a pilot project, which the present 
          application is for:
          1. The development and definition of the parameters for TEI encoding of
          Avestan bilingual manuscripts is the first objective of this pilot
          project.
          2. At present the transformation of TEI encoded XML files to the Ledmac
          format for generating typeset pages is in a preliminary and
          simplistic state. The exploration and development of this pathway is
          the second objective of this pilot project.</p>
      </projectDesc>
      <samplingDecl>
        <p>Only the MSS of the Pahlavi Yasna are collated in the pilot project.</p>
      </samplingDecl>
    </encodingDesc>
